* .-(1) There is hereby established a Board to be known as the Tanzania Agricultural Research Institute Board.
<\li1>
	* The Board shall consist of the following:
<\li2>

Powers and functions of the Board
* the Chairman, who shall be appointed by the President; and
* nine other members to be appointed by the Minister as
	* a member from  the Ministry;
	* a vice-chancellor appointed from one of a leading agriculture university;
	* a Chief Executive Officer representing private agricultural research institutes;
	* the Director of Local Government Authorities;
	* the Director General of the Tanzania Commission for Science and Technology;
	* the Director General of Tanzania Livestock Research Institute;
	* a Law Officer from the Attorney-Generalâ¢s Chambers;
	* two members with experience in agriculture representing farmersâ¢ organisations; and
	* one member with experience in agriculture representing agribusiness organizations.

Without prejudice to the generality of subsection (1), the Board shall-
* provide oversight, direction and guidance on the affairs of the Institute and ensure that adequate funds and resources are made available to the Institute to carry out its national mandate of agricultural research, development and promotion;
* review and approve, strategic plans, work plans and budgets of the Institute;
* review performance reports and approve plans for carrier development and promotion of research scientists, technicians and other staff;
* recommend to the appointing authority through the Minister, disciplinary action against the Director General;
* act as disciplinary authority over management staff of the Institute;
* act as an appellate disciplinary authority for other subordinate staff of the Institute who are not at the managerial level;
* advise the Minister on the establishment of centres as  may  be necessary for the better performance of the functions of the Institute;
* oversee the administration and accountability of funds and other assets of the Institute; and
* do all acts and things as may be, in the opinion of the Board, necessary or expedient for the proper discharge of its functions under this Act.

.-(1) There shall be a Director General of the Institute appointed by the President on the advice of the Minister from amongst persons who possess relevant qualifications and competence to manage efficiently and effectively the affairs of the Institute.
* A person shall be eligible for appointment as a Director General if that person is a citizen of Tanzania and
	* a doctorate degree in agricultural sciences from a recognized university;
	* high level of integrity;
	* proven knowledge and experience of at least ten years in matters relating to scientific research or agricultural research and development; and
	* innovative ideas with competence in good governance.
	* The Director General shall be a Secretary to the Board and shall, in the performance of his functions under this Act, be under the general supervision and control of the Board.
	* The Director General shall be the Chief Executive Officer of the Institute and shall be responsible for-
* day to day operations and affairs of the Institute;
	* developing and, subject to approval of the Board, implementation of strategic plan of the Institute;
	* mobilization and management of funds, property and business of the Institute;
	* administration, organization and control of the staff of the Institute and discipline of the employees other than management staff of the Institute;
	* coordination and implementation of policies, programmes and activities of the Institute; and
	* discharge of any other duties that may be assigned to him by the Board.
	* In the discharge of his duties under this Act or any subsidiary legislation made thereunder, the Director General shall comply with the directives of the Board as may be given from time to time.
	* The Director General shall hold office for a term of five years and shall be eligible for reappointment for one more term.
	* Officers and employees recruited under this section shall hold office on such terms and conditions as the Board may determine.

