* The research centres shall be headed by a director who shall be appointed by the Board.
* The Minister may, upon advice of the Board and by Order published in the Gazette, amend, add to, vary or replace the centres specified in the Second Schedule.
* The Forum shall consist of-
	* the Chairman appointed by the Minister from
	* other members appointed by the Minister from institutions of the national agricultural research system as
		* one member from the Ministry responsible for agriculture;
		* Chief Executive Officers from public and private research institutes dealing with agricultural research;
		* Directors responsible for research from agricultural related higher learning institutions;
		* the Director General  of Tanzania Livestock Research Institute;
		* the Director of Local Government authorities;
		* ten representative of farmers organizations;
		* a representatives  of agribusiness;
		* the Director General of the Tanzania Commission for Science and Technology;
		* the Director General of the National Environmental Management Council;

(1)  The Forum shall have the following functions-
* provide a platform for deliberation and discussions regarding challenges facing the national agricultural research system;
* provide a platform for sharing information, knowledge and best practices among national agricultural research system institutions; and

.-(1) For effective planning, implementation and impact assessment of agricultural research, the Institute shall be responsible for-
* tracking and assessing the extent of use and effectiveness of research outputs and get feedback on adoption and impact of technologies;
* institutionalizing effective peer review system;
* establishing commodity and or discipline national research coordinating committees;
* institutionalizing an effective research performance assessment system and developing results, outcome-and impact-based indicators; and
* institutionalizing an efficient progress reporting, communication and management information system.
	* The Institute shall in consultation with other relevant entities, formulate and periodically revise, a national plan for monitoring agricultural research and allied scientific research and shall undertake such monitoring activities.
<\li2>
	* The Minister may, by regulations, prescribe the manner of registering agricultural research service providers and any other matters connected thereto.
	* Any person who carries out agricultural research service without being registered pursuant to this section commits an offence.

The funds of the Institute shall be utilised for the purposes of-
* meeting costs of implementing agricultural research projects, research infrastructure development, research operational costs and commercialization of research products;
* the acquisition of land, equipment, materials and other assets;
* the training or capacity building of experts or farmers engaged in the agricultural research; and
* meeting any expenses of the Institute.
* grant gratuities or other retirement allowances or benefits to the employees of the Institute;
* establish and contribute to a superannuation fund or a medical benefits fund for the employees of the Institute;

The Board shall, within six months after the close of the financial year, cause to be prepared and submitted to the Minister a report on activities on operation s undertaken by the Institute during that financial year and accompanied
* a copy of the audited accounts;
* a copy of the auditorsâ¢ reports on the accounts; and
* such other information as the Minister may direct.
* in the case of an individual, to a fine of not less than five hundred thousand shillings and not exceeding one million shillings, or imprisonment for a term of six months or to both;
* in the case of a subsequent offence, to a further fine of not less than two million shillings and not exceeding five million shillings or imprisonment for a term of twelve months or to both;
* in the case of a corporation, to a fine of not less than one million shillings and in the case of a subsequent offence, to a further fine of not less than five million shillings.

Power to make 36.-(1) The Minister may, make regulations for the regulations better carrying out the provisions of this Act.
* Without prejudice to the generality of subsection (1), the Minister may make regulations
<\li1>
	* the registration procedures for-
		* agricultural research service providers;
		* agricultural research projects;
		* conducting agricultural research;
		* prescribing for payment of fees payable under this Act;
		* conducting monitoring and evaluation;
		* prescribing for modalities of publication of agricultural research findings;
		* the setting of standards and a code of conduct of the agricultural research service providers;
		* prescribing procedures of submission to the Institute of research project proposals;
		* prescribing procedures for contracting research;
		* prescribing the manner of maintaining  of database for agricultural  research information; other technologies by the Institute;
